Notes:

Date:  0/11/1884
Source:  NZ Journal of Science
Author:
Vol / Page:  283
Edition:
Quote:  20. <i>Sphenoecus punctatus, Quoy et Gaim</i>. Utick, Grass-bird, Matata. - At one time very commonly met with about the swamps and round the edges of lagoons where the coarse water grasses grew rankly; ... [284] Thirty years ago it was one of the most common species that affected the open country about Rockwood in the Malvern district; the lads called it `utick' from its note.
Notes:  (T.H. Potts)

